&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Emergency Nurse Practitioner/Emergency Care Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ED has fantastic opportunities for experienced ENPS and ECPs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to expansion of the team due to an enlarged ED footprint, we have some fantastic opportunities for you to join our brilliant team of autonomous practitioners&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A nurse or paramedic who is a qualified autonomous practitioner and has experience in working in urgent or emergency department settings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are experienced in managing a wide range of patients presenting with injury and illness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are keen to develop your scope of practice and depth of knowledge and skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And want to be part of an exceptional ED multidisciplinary team:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then this is the post you have been looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ENP/ECP ACP team in this inner city ED comprises of 23 autonomous practitioners delivering a high quality 24 hour service 7 days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is protected teaching each week, and a supportive culture in which to learn new skills. There are a variety of roles in the team which everyone rotates through; clinician, streaming and see and treat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ED has strong links with the local university and the Emergency Practitioner course, and MSc in Advanced Practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in further information then please contact the professional lead:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Hoskins&lt;/p&gt;
